h3. Problem Statement
{code:java}
When the Issue Picker Auto-Complete is set to off auto complete still works on certain screens like Link issue
{code}

{panel:title=Description}
Steps to Replicate:
 * Navigate to General Configuration
 * Set 'Issue Picker Auto-complete' to off
 * Navigate to Project > Select any issue > More > Link
 ** Auto-complete work as usual{panel}

{panel:title=Results}
Expected Results:
Auto-complete should not work 
Actual Results:
Auto-complete works and does not respect the configurations
{panel}

The only place where this has been working currently is, when converting a Sub-Task on Step 1 'Select Parent Issue'

As a user, we would like that the complete sprint dialog showed the sprint total and the board total, so we can have a clear understanding of what will be moved to the backlog, and what will be moved to the new sprint.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create the new scrum project. Project name - *Da;*
 # Create 6 issues. Issue names - *1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6;*
 # For the issues *2,4,6* set the fix version to *1.0;*
 # Create new sprint;
 # Move *all* the issues to a new sprint;
 # Start new sprint;
 # Move issues *3* and *4* to "*In-progress*" state;
 # Move issues *5* and *6* to "*Done*" state;
 # Change the board filter from
{code:java}
project = DA ORDER BY Rank ASC{code}
to
{code:java}
 project = DA AND fixVersion = 1.0 ORDER BY Rank ASC{code}
 # Complete the sprint and move the incomplete issues to New sprint

 

*Actual results*
 Complete sprint dialog shows a number of the issues in the sprint (Reference: JSWSERVER-20484
{panel}
*Complete Sprint DA Sprint 1*

2 issues were done
 4 issues were incomplete

Select where all the incomplete issues should be moved:
 Move to : <new sprint | Backlog>
{panel}
 

*Desired results, for User has a full view of the Sprint situation*
{panel}
*Complete Sprint DA Sprint 1*

2 issues were done
 2 issues out of the board were incomplete and will be moved to the backlog
 2 board issues were incomplete

Select where all the incomplete board issues from the board should be moved:
 Move to: <new sprint | Backlog>
{panel}

h3. Problem Definition
While Jira 8 has made great strides in performance, there remain a few operations that are regularly 5+ seconds. I'm singling out Epic Link query performance because I'm noticing this is one of our top-ranked common operations. This can cause delays and block stories from being created when the Epic Link is a required field on the create screen. 

h3. Steps to reproduce
You can experience this when you:
# Edit an Issue
#  fill out the `E_pic Link_` value
#* Jira will generate the XHR request -{{/rest/greenhopper/1.0/epics}}

h3. Suggested Solution
Epic data loads within 3 seconds. 

